# GitLab

You can use Buildkite to run builds on [GitLab](https://about.gitlab.com/) commits.

<%= toc %>

## gitlab.com repositories

If you are hosting your repositories on [gitlab.com](https://gitlab.com/) enter your gitlab.com repository URL when you create your pipeline in Buildkite (e.g. `git@gitlab.com:your/repo.git`) and then follow the instructions provided on that page.

## Self-hosted GitLab repositories

Firstly, ensure you're using at least [GitLab version 7.4](https://about.gitlab.com/2014/10/22/gitlab-7-4-released/). If you are, you can head straight to your **Account settings** page on Buildkite.

Find the **GitLab (Self Hosted)** section and specify which GitLab edition you're using (Community or Enterprise), and enter the URL to your GitLab installation (e.g. `https://git.mycompany.com`).

<%= image "form.png", width: 1436/2, height: 668/2, alt: "Screen of Buildkite Organiziation GitLab Settings" %>

Then click **Save GitLab Settings**.

Create a new pipeline on Buildkite using your Gitlab repository's URL (e.g. `git@git.mycompany.com:your/repo.git`) and then follow the instructions on the pipeline creation page.
